<paragraph blockId="4.[151,616,477,504]" box="[151,616,477,504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,616,477,504]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Luc, Taylor &amp; Cadet, 1978" authorityName="Luc, Taylor &amp; Cadet" authorityYear="1978" box="[151,616,477,504]" class="Secernentea" family="Heteroderidae" genus="Hylonema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tylenchida" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,616,477,504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,477,504]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Hylonema</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Taylor, D. P. &amp; Cadet, P. &amp; Luc, M." box="[284,616,477,503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" pagination="99 - 108" refId="ref11236" refString="Taylor, D. P., Cadet, P. &amp; Luc, M. (1978) A unique host-relationship between Hylonema ivorense (Nematoda: Heteroderidae) and the roots of a tropical rainforest tree. Revue de Nematologie, 1, 99 - 108." type="journal article" year="1978">Luc, Taylor &amp; Cadet, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,549,971]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">
The only species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Luc, Taylor &amp; Cadet, 1978" authorityName="Luc, Taylor &amp; Cadet" authorityYear="1978" box="[353,790,549,575]" class="Secernentea" family="Heteroderidae" genus="Hylonema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tylenchida" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="ivorense">
<emphasis box="[353,481,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">H. ivorense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Taylor, D. P. &amp; Cadet, P. &amp; Luc, M." box="[487,790,549,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" pagination="99 - 108" refId="ref11236" refString="Taylor, D. P., Cadet, P. &amp; Luc, M. (1978) A unique host-relationship between Hylonema ivorense (Nematoda: Heteroderidae) and the roots of a tropical rainforest tree. Revue de Nematologie, 1, 99 - 108." type="journal article" year="1978">Luc, Taylor &amp; Cadet, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was recovered from roots of “avodiré” (
<taxonomicName authority="Pellegr." authorityName="Pellegr." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Turraeanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Turraeanthus africana</emphasis>
Pellegr.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="de Jussieu, 1789" authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[329,446,585,612]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Meliaceae</taxonomicName>
) from a tropical rainforest reserve of the Banco National Park, near 
<collectingRegion box="[1202,1295,585,611]" country="Ivory Coast" name="Abidjan" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Abidjan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1305,1436,585,611]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Luc, M. &amp; Taylor, D. P. &amp; Cadet, P." box="[159,334,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" pagination="73 - 86" refId="ref9672" refString="Luc, M., Taylor, D. P. &amp; Cadet, P. (1978) Description of a new tropical Heteroderidae, Hylonema ivorense n. gen., n. sp., and a new outlook on the family Heteroderidae (Nematoda: Tylenchida). Revue de Nematologie, 1, 73 - 86." type="journal article" year="1978">
Luc 
<emphasis box="[211,268,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">et al.</emphasis>
1978
</bibRefCitation>
). It was also found in a forest soil sample in 
<collectingCountry box="[836,967,621,647]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fortuner, R. &amp; Couturier, G." box="[982,1290,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" pagination="3 - 10" refId="ref8406" refString="Fortuner, R. &amp; Couturier, G. (1983) Les nematodes parasites de plantes de la foret de Tai (Cote d'Ivoire). Revue de Nematologie, 6, 3 - 10. [in French]" type="journal article" year="1983">Fortuner &amp; Couturier 1983</bibRefCitation>
). The known range of the species was expanded after it was recovered in the Korup National Park, 
<collectingCountry box="[1126,1243,657,683]" name="Cameroon" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Price, N. S. &amp; Siddiqi, M. R." pageId="4" pageNumber="343" pagination="117 - 128" refId="ref10417" refString="Price, N. S. &amp; Siddiqi, M. R. (1994) Rainforest nematodes with particular reference to the Korup National Park, Cameroon. Afro- Asian Journal of Nematology, 4, 117 - 128." type="journal article" year="1994">Price &amp; Siddiqi 1994</bibRefCitation>
). In one soil sample collected in a rainforest in Kribi, 
<collectingCountry box="[817,937,693,719]" name="Cameroon" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, some heteroderid J2s were found with morphological characters close to those of the 
<typeStatus box="[628,676,729,755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">type</typeStatus>
population (
<bibRefCitation author="Sturhan, D." box="[817,974,729,755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref10861" refString="Sturhan, D. (2018) Diagnostic and phylogenetic significance of lateral field incisures, phasmids and other morphological characters of second-stage juveniles and males of Heteroderidae (Nematoda, Tylenchida), with notes on hosts and phylogeography. Russian Journal of Nematology, 26, 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="2018">Sturhan 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="343" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,549,971]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luc, Taylor &amp; Cadet" authorityYear="1978" box="[199,331,766,791]" class="Secernentea" family="Heteroderidae" genus="Hylonema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tylenchida" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="ivorense">
<emphasis box="[199,331,766,791]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">H. ivorense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
induces a uninucleate giant cell in roots of its 
<typeStatus box="[891,939,765,791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">type</typeStatus>
host. Histological examination of infected avodiré roots showed that each female incited production of only one giant cell, with the nucleus of each giant cell greatly enlarged, up to 200 times the volume of a normal nucleus, and each nucleus containing an enlarged nucleolus, which is itself usually larger than a healthy nucleus. No discrete cell wall was observed surrounding the giant cell (
<bibRefCitation author="Taylor, D. P. &amp; Cadet, P. &amp; Luc, M." box="[208,420,909,935]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" pagination="99 - 108" refId="ref11236" refString="Taylor, D. P., Cadet, P. &amp; Luc, M. (1978) A unique host-relationship between Hylonema ivorense (Nematoda: Heteroderidae) and the roots of a tropical rainforest tree. Revue de Nematologie, 1, 99 - 108." type="journal article" year="1978">
Taylor 
<emphasis box="[292,351,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">et al.</emphasis>
1978
</bibRefCitation>
). In another study, rice (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linneo" authorityYear="1753" box="[704,848,909,935]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Oryza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativa">
<emphasis box="[704,848,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">Oryza sativa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sturhan" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[898,992,909,935]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) was considered as a non-host for this nematode (
<bibRefCitation author="Coyne, D. L. &amp; Thio, B. &amp; Plowright, R. A. &amp; Hunt, D. J." box="[275,479,945,971]" pageId="4" pageNumber="343" pagination="433 - 441" refId="ref8179" refString="Coyne, D. L., Thio, B., Plowright, R. A. &amp; Hunt, D. J. (1999) Observations on the community dynamics of plant parasitic nematodes of rice in Cote d'Ivoire. Nematology, 1, 433 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854199508324" type="journal article" year="1999">
Coyne 
<emphasis box="[356,413,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="343">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
